A Prince George’s County corrections officer has been arrested and charged in connection with an attack on his wife in their home in Charles County, authorities said. The woman was handcuffed, shackled and stabbed repeatedly during the attack Friday in the couple’s home in Bryans Road, the Charles County sheriff’s office said. Her husband, Armando Quispe Rodriguez, 45, was arrested Monday and charged with attempted murder, assault, and false imprisonment, the sheriff’s office said. A spokeswoman for the Prince George’s corrections department said the suspect has worked there for 19 years. She said he would be placed on leave without pay. His wife was in serious condition Tuesday, the Charles County sheriff’s office said.